Come on Richard!  I'm just a shot up old helicopter pilot with schrapnel all in his feet... lots of nightmares from killing children.  Intrusive thoughts about dead friends and other horrors.  I'm highly pissed at the Army and Navy...U.S. Congress... and anybody who don't ride a Harley.<br><br>
Did five years of service as an enlisted man before going to flight school for a year...served nine months in combat before receiving my draft notice in Viet Nam.  Boy was I pissed!  I didn't even get a chance to run!  Too late now to cry over spilled milk.<br><br>
I would like to know how hard it was on you to stay in Canada during the war.. I heard that winters there are worse than Korea.<br><br>
What did you do all that time... mooch off the Canadians or make an honest living stealing and selling drugs..?<br><br>
Geez...Disappearing Dick.. you must have some really exciting stories to tell.  Have you applied for any government benefits for your hardships?  I suffer from PTSD, residuals of five gunshot wounds and a broken back secondary to two years of intensive combat... you can claim a personality disorder secondary to being a gutless coward.. after all... the government caused both our problems.<br><br>
Sunny Delight... Gotcha in my sight!<br><br>
